Comment: strengthtopursue said "Soaking more almonds so I can make more almond milk in the morning.

Take 1 cup almonds & rinse. Soak in 3 cups spring or filtered water (overnight or during the day while you are at work). Do not use regular tap water. Impurities in the water will soak into almonds. 
Rinse almonds after soak and place them into blender with 4 cups fresh, filtered water, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon. You can add real maple syrup to give it a sweet kick but I love it without.
Once blended, pour through a nut bag (cheesecloth will work but you will have almond bits) in a bowl that is large enough to hold 4 cups.
Squeeze bag until all liquid has been extracted. Transfer to a container and store in fridge. It will keep about 5-7 days.
Enjoy!
#easytomake #almondmilk #homemade"

Is it a story weâ€™ve told ourselves for so long that we can no longer see straight? Our strong fixed beliefs, opinions and habits are just allowing us to live our lives on autopilot? 
What would it take for you to not allow it anymore? What would it take to live as your brightest, best self? To dump the negativity, to throw out the story, to break up with the lifelong friend that only dims your light? 
This month, Iâ€™ve had two heartbreaking breakups. The craziest part is that the lead up to these breakups were SO MUCH WORSE than the actual breakup itself. The friendships were ones I had for quite some time, both of which were not serving either person fully. Once we decided a separation was the best thing for us, everything just felt better. Calmer.

Comment: rippedlikenick said "Starting this week, I'm posting my daily tips on proper deadlift form. Personally, I think DL are a great workout routine that adds lean mass and give you the strongman look. It was very popular back in the day, but then lost its traction with the weightlifting community. However, within the past few years because of the popularity of crossfit, DL and other power lifting routines are making a comeback. While I applaud the efforts of gym newbies attempting powerlifting, I often cringed when looking at them doing the routines. Comment: thetacohunters said "A hop, skip and a jump from Helmâ€™s Bakers in Culver on W. Washington is this colorful little orange #taco gem known as EK Valley Restaurant. The small oaxacan restaurant really brightens up the block with its flavorful tacos and other oaxacan dishes. I ordered the combo plate which includes rice, beans and or salad and two tacos of your choosing. I decided to try their salmon taco and chorizo taco, my friend had their carnitas and chicken tacos! The rice was a deep orange color and extremely flavorful and well seasoned. The beans were topped with a little crumble cheese and very delicious. The chorizo taco was very moist and these tacos are served up with the traditional double tortilla.  Good thing because the meat is juicy and their tends to be many salsas, sauces and creams used in these taco dishes. The salmon taco was cooked perfectly, and has a unique flavor, and is a excellent alternative to your more typical fried fish taco. Same for the chicken tacos, moist, tasty and well seasoned. Carnitas were def not my favorite I thought it was a little dry for my taste. Rutt's Hawaiian Cafe & Catering in Culver City, California serves up this famous dish of theirs: The Hawaiian Royale. An open scrambled Omlette over White Rice served with a side of Teriyaki Sauce. All Royales are served with Onions & Bean Sprouts & Char Sui (Char Siu). Mine's here is with Portugese Sausage. 
Make sure to Ask for Your Free Roll. Always free upon request. 
Some Spam Masubi & some Hawaiian Sun Guava Juice completes this Yummy Meal. 
Many combonations of meats & rice offered. Veggies & Tofu also served."

Rutt's Hawaiian Cafe & Catering in Culver City, California serves up this famous dish of theirs: The Hawaiian Royale. An open scrambled Omlette over White Rice served with a side of Teriyaki Sauce. All Royales are served with Onions & Bean Sprouts & Char Sui (Char Siu). Mine's here is with Portugese Sausage. 
Make sure to Ask for Your Free Roll. Always free upon request. 
Some Spam Masubi & some Hawaiian Sun Guava Juice completes this Yummy Meal. 
Many combonations of meats & rice offered. Veggies & Tofu also served. 
Featured on both Cheap Eats TV as well as Diners, Drive-ins & Dives with Guy Fieri (featuring Gene Simmons)"

Rutt's Hawaiian Cafe & Catering in Culver City, California serves up this famous dish of theirs: The Hawaiian Royale. An open scrambled Omlette over White Rice served with a side of Teriyaki Sauce. All Royales are served with Onions & Bean Sprouts & Char Sui (Char Siu). Mine's here is with Portugese Sausage. 
Make sure to Ask for Your Free Roll. Always free upon request. 
Some Spam Masubi & some Hawaiian Sun Guava Juice completes this Yummy Meal. 
Many combonations of meats & rice offered. Veggies & Tofu also served. 
Featured on both Cheap Eats TV as well as Diners, Drive-ins & Dives with Guy Fieri (featuring Gene Simmons)"

Comment: thegothicrestaurant said "RECIPE SHARE. Trumpet Mushroom "Scallops" with BBQ Miso Glaze. BBQ MISO: 1/2 cup white miso paste | 1/2 cup Nama shoyu | 1/2 cup agave nectar | 2 tablespoons apple cider vinegar | 2 tablespoons lemon juice | 2 tablespoons water | 2 teaspoons sesame oil. Blend all ingredients until smooth. ASSEMBLY: Take approx 1 dozen large king trumpet mushrooms and slice off both ends, leaving a fairly even white stalk to work with. Slice crosswise into 1/2 inch medallions. Toss scallops with enough glaze to coat evenly and marinate for 30 minutes before serving. If desired, drizzle with additional glaze."

Comment: noelleseybert said "On the West coast we spend a lot of time marveling at the beauty of the unending horizon and the sheer vastness that is the ocean. I found myself doing that in my car before leaving @Pepperdine tonight and snapped a photo (and shared on Pepp's insta) thinking how the West's horizon is something I gravitate to and also stresses me out. 
But why? It's only opportunity. It's essentially the future. The sun/moon I see, hasn't made it "there" yet. However, I feel like we rarely look East and think the same positive thoughts about its existence. 
That's the past and holds the same level of beauty, just a different type. It got me thinking. I have come so far in the last two and a half years since leaving San Diego with many hiccups along the way, but I've made it. LA is home. 
I can continue to look East and try to make it as pretty as the West, but why? The view due West doesn't need any work to make it gorgeous. 
Onward."

Comment: orlee said "How is it that when we stand on one leg with our eyes open, we can find the balance? And then how is it that when we close our eyes, the balance is lost? If you think about it,  there is no reason why the balance should be lost. Nothing has changed. The environment you stand on that one leg is still the same and your ability to balance is still the same. So what's changed? Consider, everything outside of your eyes, outside of you, you hold on to. You are so crazily attached that it seems impossible without your environment holding you up. Consider, there is a whole other environment within you that if you allow, you can find that support within as well. It's a different world inside, but it's there... I think we forget that because you don't see anything when you shut your eyes, so it would seem as though you are in nothing and so, you get lost.... Except that nothing is everything and so that makes everything possible... Even standing on one leg. Come get lost within tomorrow 7a power 1 @hot8yoga #beverlyhills, 9:45a barre @qtfitness #pacificpalisades, 6:45p power flow @sohoyoga #hermosabeach #betyousweat #yoga #yogaeverydamnday"

This little blue pen has run out of ink. That makes me happy and sad and disappointed and excited all at the same time. Happy because I committed that much ink to paper. Sad because what I did with it probably wasn't all that great. Disappointed because it took me a helluva' lot longer than it should've. Comment: charitygirlproblems said ""You can learn a lot of things from the flowers...all in the golden afternoon." I've always loved Alice In Wonderland, but his quote has become more relevant as I've grown older. We truly can learn a lot of things from the flowers; many grow in tough circumstances and still stay delicate. 
Bo matter how delicate or short their life, flowers still bloom vividly, And are celebrated for their bright beauty. We, as humans, should live the same way. Live as brightly as we can, no matter how long or short our life is, or how delicate we think we are. Be bold. Be bright. Be beautiful. Be brave. Be delicate. All these attributes combined leave good things in their wake. 
Thanks #KatieSchellenberg and @bloomthat for the reminder of how important it is to be bold, delicate and fierce.

Its bulging eyes, long goblin-like ears, and crooked smile serve only to vex any audience that attempts to make sense out of it. Ingredients:
ğŸ”¸choice of caviar
ğŸ”¸sour cream
ğŸ”¸1 medium avocado, diced
ğŸ”¸2.5 tsp. lemon juice
ğŸ”¸3/4 tsp. fresh dill
ğŸ”¸salt & pepper
ğŸ”¸cherry tomatoes, quartered
ğŸ”¸crÃ¨me fraÃ®che
ğŸ”¸blinis or crackers

Directions:
1. Spoon sour cream into a ziploc bag. Cut a small hole in the corner of the bag. Pipe the sour cream into an appetizer dish or shot glass.
2. Combine avocado, lemon juice, chopped dill; mash with a fork until smooth. Mix in desired amount of salt and pepper to taste.
3. Spoon avocado mixture into a ziploc bag; repeat the piping process on top of the layer of sour cream.
4. Top the layers with tomatoes, a dollop of crÃ¨me fraÃ®che and caviar. Serve with blinis or crackers!"

Comment: thorfitness22 said "Week 3 and 4 are the same, built to increase functional strength and stability which is very important. Focus on your form while drawing in your core as if someone was about to jab you in the stomach + squeeze the imaginary dollar between the glutes. For beginners 4 sets might be too much volume at 12-20 reps of all exercises so try for 2-3 sets. This workout is a full body split routine so expect soreness and make sure you are controlling your nutrition accordingly as well as communicate with your doctor. Keep in mind this program is built for myself so take at your own experience level and capabilities as far as exercises and weight. If you have questions about certain exercises feel free to comment or youtube the exercise because I abbreviated the names for myself"

Comment: thorfitness22 said "Now week 11-12 are by far the hardest to get through, a german volume set will put on serious mass its 10 sets of 10 with a minute rest in between sets at about 75-80% intensity. Your body will be extremely sore after this and your will probably be feeling it for days so make sure to sleep eat hydrate and recover properly. This program is not necessary for everyone if you are not trying to gain super size so if not you can continue these workouts at 5-6 sets of 10. This workout targets one muscle group in depth per day so its a 3 day split. If you can complete all the exercixes at 10 x 10 congatdulations but if not you want to hit the main exercise groups such as bench military press pulldowns rows squats deadlifts and hip thrust to get the benefit then complete 5-6 sets of the other exercises. For week 12 if you want to try something a little different to engage bigger muscle fibers, increase the weight to 80-85% and do 10 sets of 6-8......Good luck and let me know your pre and post thoughts on this workout have fun lol Keep in mind this program is built for myself so take at your own experience level and capabilities as far as exercises and weight. If you have questions about certain exercises feel free to comment or youtube the exercise because I abbreviated the names for myself  #gym #stability #workout #exercise #strength #strengthandconditioning #fitness #weightloss #muscle #speed #agility #training #personaltrainer #codybtraining #THORfitness #crossfit #programdesign #germanvolume"

Comment: matthewjphotos said "After an amazing cruise at Milford Sound, our return journey back to Queenstown via Highway 6 hugged right along the peaceful and serene Lake Wakitipu. We had just passed by the town of Kingston, the southern most town on the lake, and pulled over to take some pics. While the morning had started off sunny and clear, the rest of the time was a mix of overcast skies, clouds and heavy rain on and off throughout the day. This patch of clouds just hung in the air, stationary and immobile, while the aqua blue and green waters lay peaceful and calm underneath. I could have sat here until dark, just soaking this all in, but our stomachs were telling us otherwise. A nice hearty dinner back in Queenstown was awaiting us after a long day of exploration across the beautiful landscape that is New Zealand.

Comment: depaulfitness said "We have a system of receptor nerves (proprioceptors) located in the muscles, joints, and ligaments. These receptors can sense changes just as other receptors monitor pressure, sound, heat, light, etc., and pass that information to the brain. The brain returns a message to the affected muscles telling them what to do.Â This canÂ happen so fast that it's, at times, referred to as a reflex rather than a reaction.

There's a fine line between proprioception and kinesthetic awareness. Although some people use the terms interchangeably, there is a difference. Kinesthetic aware is a conscious effort to react to the situation, while proprioception is an unconscious or subconscious process.

The two mechanisms work together to allow a smooth, efficient, and safe platform for movement and athletic performance. Example, a skier whose body acts subconsciously (proprioception) to stay upright while the mind (kinesthetic awareness) processes data regarding slopes, bumps, trees,Â speed, and anything else he or she needs to make necessary. Well-designed movement drills further develop the neuromuscular pathways that enhance performance and prevent injuries."

100 students from Raul Isidro Burgos Rural Teachers College traveled to Iguala, Mexico to hold protest for what they considered discriminatory hiring and funding practices from the government. During the journey, local police intercepted them. Details of what happened remain uncertain, but during the police clash 6 people were killed, 25 were wounded and 43 male students went missing. Latin 
Inter
